issue.body:
I have a weird issue with class-wp-job-manager-settings.php.
I'm using Wordpress 6.3.2 and PHP 8.0.30.

PHP Warning: foreach() argument must be of type array|object, string given in /wp-content/plugins/wp-job-manager/includes/admin/class-wp-job-manager-settings.php on line 1143

The issue happens in the function get_capabilities_and_roles( $caps = [] ) when $caps == 0 (empty).
I have not set any custom user selected capabilities. 

The only way to resolve is to check if $caps is emty (see code below).
Is this a known issue?

* Get the list of roles and capabilities to use in select dropdown.
        *
        * @param array $caps Selected capabilities to ensure they show up in the list.
        * @return array
        */
       private static function get_capabilities_and_roles( $caps = [] ) {
               $capabilities_and_roles = [];
               $roles                 = get_editable_roles();
               foreach ( $roles as $key => $role ) {
                       $capabilities_and_roles[ $key ] = $role[‘name’];
               }

               **if( sizeof($caps) != 0 ) { /// <— THIS!**

                  // Go through custom user selected capabilities and add them to the list.
                  foreach ( $caps as $value ) {
                          if ( isset( $capabilities_and_roles[ $value ] ) ) {
                                 continue;
                          }
                          $capabilities_and_roles[ $value ] = $value;
                  }
               }

               return $capabilities_and_roles;

       }
